This directory contains version 3.0 of SB-Prolog.  It has
essentially the functionality of version 2.5, but has been
rewritten so that it runs on alignment-restricted processors
like Sun-4, Pyramid-98x, DEC3100 and SGI Iris.  

    Files in the directory v3.0 are compressed.  Use BINARY
    mode to ftp them.
    ------------------------------------------------------------------
(0) A General Public License for SB-Prolog is in the file COPYING.

(1) Change the variable SBPDIR in the file v3.0/INIT to the full path
    name of the sbprolog directory, e.g., /usr/local/sbprolog/v3.0 or
    /u9/sr/pub/sbprolog/v3.0, etc.

(2) To install SB-Prolog, execute (cd v3.0; source INSTALL)

(3) For an SB-Prolog User Manual, execute the command

	tbl sbprolog_doc.me | itroff -me

(4) The Prolog byte code files in cmplib, lib and
    modlib should not have to be recompiled except under
    exceptional circumstances (such as corruption
    during transmission), as they are machine independent.

(5) The subdirectory v3.0 contains version 3.0, which will 
    run on alignment-restricted processors like Sun-4, Iris,
    or DEC3100. Currently (Aug 1989), there are only very
    minor (outward) differences between v2.5 and v3.0 -- two
    that I know about are that (i) v3.0 still requires explicit
    pragma files for indexing; and (ii) in v3.0, cuts within
    if-then-elses are soft (in v2.5 they are hard).

---
